  "prompt": "What do I do if my best friend is dating my crush?",
  "response": "Dealing with a situation where your best friend is dating your crush can be challenging and emotionally complex. Here are some steps you might consider to navigate this situation:\n\n1. **Process Your Emotions:** Take some time to acknowledge and understand your feelings. It\u2019s normal to feel hurt, jealous, or disappointed.\n\n2. **Give Yourself Space:** If needed, take a little distance from both your friend and your crush to allow yourself space to reflect and heal. It's important to not make any hasty decisions based on immediate emotions.\n\n3. **Evaluate Your Priorities:** Consider what is more important to you: your friendship or your feelings for your crush. This can help guide your actions moving forward.\n\n4. **Open Communication:** If you feel comfortable, talk to your best friend about your feelings. Use \"I\" statements to express how you feel without making them feel attacked. For example, \"I feel hurt because I had strong feelings for [crush's name].\"\n\n5. **Respect Their Relationship:** If your friend and your crush are happy together, it\u2019s respectful to acknowledge their relationship and give them space. Avoid trying to come between them.\n\n6. **Focus on Yourself:** Channel your energy into personal growth and activities that make you happy. This can help you move forward and heal.\n\n7. **Seek Support:** Talk to other friends, family members, or a counselor about your feelings. Sometimes an outside perspective can provide comfort and guidance.\n\nRemember that relationships can be complicated, and handling them with maturity and respect will likely lead to better outcomes for everyone involved.",
